track_notes:
Car park machine frequently broken, otherwise Â£3 for the day. Start of path leads across open ground through small forest before climbing proper. Route is easy to follow to the saddle beside Meikle Pap. Route from the saddle up requires scramble through small boulder field. Once on top its easy going following ridge to summit. Phone signal only found at ridge edge with line of site to Ballater and before ascending to the saddle. Cornices near edge of particular concern during winter.
Southerly return option down Glas Allt path available to escape summit conditions, recently refurbished path with steps. Leads past the Queens Bothy at Glas-allt-Shiel. Entrance besides coal shed at back of building. Caution, bothy has been recently locked during the pandemic due to abuse. Path follows loch to return to car park.
This summit is a personal favourite.
track_title: Lochnagar from Spittal of Glenmuick car park.

track_notes:
Best to cycle from the castle to the mid-point of Conachcraig and Lochnagar, then you can walk up both summits.

Nice fast route home on the bike!
